ion of annual spring burning and intensive early stocking is likely depressing survival of greater prairie?chickens in the Flint Hills ecoregion. Our results join a growing body of evidence that patch?burn grazing can provide higher quality grassland habitats for native wildlife species than current rangeland management associated with intensive cattle production. ? 2017 The Wildlife Society},
